        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 18 at 6:35AM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 635 AM MDT, An area of snow showers was tracking across the Big
Horns and also over the Sheridan foothills from Aberdeen Hill to
south of Sheridan. Visibility will be reduced at times to under a
mile with up to an inch of accumulation possible before tapering off
after 8 am.

Locations impacted include...
I-25 from Aberdeen Hill to south of Sheridan and including
Sheridan, Ranchester, Dayton, Big Horn, Banner and Story.
</description>
        <instruction>Motorists should use caution and be alert for slippery conditions
and limited visibility. Plan on extra time for the morning commute.</instruction>
